race.comment: ALMANZAS (3) returns a gelding for the Baker yard. Left himself with too much to do in both runs in his debut prep, but was warming nicely late. Readied with a pair of trials and gets the blinkers applied first time. Can return with a bang. Stablemate SINISTER (5) is a son of Savabeel on debut. Has trialled up nicely in readiness and is well placed to make a bright start. SHARBINO (14) found it too tough in town at the latest when always well back. Finds a suitable assignment this time and deserves following up. BRAINIAC (7) is mixing her form but has shown glimpses of ability. Gets in light with the claim and is drawn low. Have to include.
